The '''A528''' is a route on the [[United Kingdom|UK]] highway network that runs from [[Marchwiel]], near [[Wrexham]], in [[North Wales]] {{nowrap|({{coord|53.0225|-2.9597|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline|name=A528 road (northern end)}}),}} to [[Shrewsbury]], [[Shropshire]], in [[England]] {{nowrap|({{coord|52.7128|-2.7512|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline|name=A528 road (southern end)}}).}} On the way it passes through [[Ellesmere, Shropshire|Ellesmere]] and [[Coton Hill, Shropshire|Coton Hill]]. The road follows an old route that was Turnpiked in the 18th century.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Williams|first1=Paul|title=A watching brief on the A5124 Battlefield Link Road, Shrewsbury|url=http://archaeologydataservice.ac.uk/archiveDS/archiveDownload?t=arch-1016-1/dissemination/pdf/A5124_BATTLIFIELD_LINK_RD.pdf|website=archaeologydataservice.ac.uk|publisher=ADS|accessdate=6 February 2017|page=4|language=en|format=PDF|date=November 1998}}</ref>

==Route==
The road starts {{convert|4|km|order=flip}} south east of Wrexham at Marchwiel by a junction on the [[A525 road]].<ref>{{cite map|title =Wrexham & Llangollen|map =256|date =2015|scale =1:25,000 |series =Explorer |publisher =Ordnance Survey|isbn = 9780319244524 }}</ref> It heads due south through Cock Bank and [[Overton Bridge]] before combining with the A539 road and going eastwards through the village of Overton-on-Dee.

It then heads south east through to Ellesmere, where it shares a small section of road with the [[A495 road|A495]], before heading south through Crosemere, [[Harmer Hill]], [[Albrighton, Shrewsbury|Albrighton]] and intersecting with the [[A5124 road|A5124]] at Harlescott north east of Shrewsbury.

The final short section into Shrewsbury goes over the [[Shrewsbury-Chester line|Shrewsbury-Chester]] railway line and intersects with the [[A5191 road (Great Britain)|A5191]] in Shrewsbury town centre. A small stub going northwards only (due to the one-way system in Shrewsbury) starts off the [[A458 road]].<ref>{{cite map|title =Collins Britain Big Road Atlas 2009|year =2008|scale =1:200,000|publisher =Collins Bartholomew|page =88|isbn =978-0-00-727240-2}}</ref>

==Safety==
The A528 is one of Wales' most riskiest and dangerous routes. It is third behind the A44 and the A5 for the number of road casualties per year.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Owen|first1=Cathy|title=The most dangerous roads in Wales revealed|url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/most-dangerous-roads-wales-revealed-10056959|accessdate=6 February 2017|work=walesonline|date=15 September 2015}}</ref>

