{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Arensky Glacier | other_name = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = Antarctic Peninsula#Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Arensky Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Alexander Island]] | coordinates = {{coord|71|39|S|72|15|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = {{convert|3|nmi|0|abbr=on}} | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Boccherini Inlet]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Arensky Glacier''' ({{coord|71|39|S|72|15|W|type:glacier_region:AQ_source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is an [[Antarctic]] [[glacier]], lying {{convert|3|mi|0}} east of [[Alyabiev Glacier]] and flows south from [[Beethoven Peninsula]], [[Alexander Island]], into the north end of [[Boccherini Inlet]]. The glacier was named by the [[USSR Academy of Sciences]] in 1987, after [[Anton Arensky]], the Russian composer.
