[[File:Galvanometro astatico di tipo Nobili inv 1417 IF 38380.jpg|thumb|Astatic galvanometer, Nobili pattern at the Museo Galileo, Florence.]]

An '''astatic system''' comprises two equal and parallel magnetic needles, but with their [[Magnet#Pole naming conventions|polarities]] reversed. This arrangement protects the system from the influence of the [[terrestrial magnetic field]], as the [[magnetisms]] of the two needles cancel each other out. Because of this phenomenon, astatic needles were often used in [[galvanometer]]s.

