Portland '''Bowers Basebed''' is a type of [[limestone]] from [[Bowers Quarry]] at the [[Isle of Portland]] in [[Dorset]], southern [[England]], on the [[Jurassic Coast]], a [[World Heritage Site]].<ref name="federation-stone">{{cite web| url=http://www.stonefed.org.uk/index.php?page=portland-bowers-basebed | title=Portland Bowers Basebed | publisher=Federation Stone Great Britain| accessdate=14 April 2013 }}</ref>

The stone is clear of fossils and is the cleanest of the [[Portland stone]] types. Bowers Basebed, which is quarried by Albion Stone, has a maximum bed height of 1.95 metres. It is known for being highly durable and being able to withstand the effects of weathering.{{fact|date=April 2013}}

Bowers Basebed was used to construct "7–10 [[Old Bailey]]", in the city of [[London]].{{fact|date=April 2013}}

