The '''British Pteridological Society''' is for [[fern]] enthusiasts of the [[British Isles]], and was founded in England in 1891.<ref name="BPS">{{cite web | url=http://www.eBPS.org.uk | title=Introduction to the BPS | author=British Pteridological Society | date= | publisher=British Pteridological Society | accessdate=2009-11-03 }}</ref>
The origins and early history of the BPS at the time of "[[Pteridomania]]" is described in the book ''The Victorian Fern Craze''.<ref name="The Victorian Fern Craze">{{cite book |last1 = Allen |first1 = David Elliston |title = The Victorian Fern Craze |publisher = [[Hutchinson (publisher)|Hutchinson]] |year = 1969 |isbn =978-0-09-099870-8}}</ref> The BPS celebrated its centenary in 1991; amongst other things, it was marked by the publication of the book, ''A World of Ferns''.<ref name="A World of Ferns">{{cite book |last1 = Camus |first1 = Josephine |last2= A. Clive |first2 = Jermy |last3= Thomas |first3 = Barry A. |title = A World of Ferns |publisher = [[Natural History Museum, London|Natural History Museum]] Publications |year = 1991 |isbn = 0-565-01120-0}}</ref>
The British Pteridological Society is a registered charity: No. 1092399.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.charity-commission.gov.uk/ShowCharity/RegisterOfCharities/CharityWithoutPartB.aspx?RegisteredCharityNumber=1092399&SubsidiaryNumber=0 |title=Register of Charities |author= |date= |work= |publisher= |accessdate=2009-11-03 }}</ref> The BPS has as its Patron HRH The Prince of Wales.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.princeofwales.gov.uk/personalprofiles/theprinceofwales/patronages/|title=The Prince of Wales - Patronages|author=|date=|work=|publisher=|accessdate=2009-11-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081020021842/http://www.princeofwales.gov.uk/personalprofiles/theprinceofwales/patronages/#|archive-date=2008-10-20|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
==Publications== The British Pteridological Society publishes a number of works, which promote pteridology: * ''The Fern Gazette'' * ''The Pteridologist'' * ''The Bulletin''
==Presidents of the Society== John A. Wilson (1831-1914) was elected Chairman of the Society at the first meeting in 1891; subsequently Dr. F.W. Stansfield was invited to become the first President of the Society. He took office in 1892.<ref name="The History of British pteridology 1891-1991">{{cite book |last=Busby |first=A.R. |editor-first=Josephine |editor-last=Camus |title=The History of British Pteridology 1891-1991 |publisher=The British Pteridological Society |date=1991 |chapter=Gleanings from the Minute Book 1891-1991 |isbn=0-9509806-3-3}}</ref>
